#DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala says R30-million has been allocated to restore water supply following deadly floods in the province. Zikalala gave an update on relief measures and progress in the province. READ: KZN Floods | Death toll climbs to 461 Meanwhile, the death toll in the April floods has risen to 461. 87 People remain missing and teams will continue searching for those people.